  {
    "index": 3,
    "hash": "ip7anDAS9Smdh4UtECW3SxMUSy8=",
    "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:29.000Z",
    "action": {
      "type": "SET_CONTENT",
      "input": {
        "content": "## Collab adapter API \u2014 `window.ph.swarm.collab`\n\nThe collaboration surface lives under a new namespace on the global adapter:\n\n```typescript\ninterface SwarmCollab {\n  /** Create a new collab. Mines GSOC signers in the background and\n   *  returns immediately. */\n  create(input: {\n    target: { driveId: string; documentId?: string };\n    participants: string[];  // Swarm signer addresses\n    caption?: string;\n  }): Promise<CollabSummary>;\n\n  /** Accept an invitation received via chat. */\n  accept(inviteRef: {\n    collabId: string;\n    manifestRef: string;\n    actHistoryAddress: string;\n    publisherBeeNodePubKey: string;\n  }): Promise<CollabSummary>;\n\n  /** Locally stop participating. Future: propagate to initiator. */\n  leave(collabId: string): Promise<void>;\n\n  /** Snapshot of all collaborations the user is part of. */\n  list(): CollabSummary[];\n\n  /** Subscribe to changes (op arrived, participant joined/left). */\n  on(event: \"updated\", handler: (s: CollabSummary) => void): () => void;\n}\n\ntype CollabSummary = {\n  collabId: string;\n  kind: \"drive\" | \"document\";\n  driveId: string;\n  documentId?: string;\n  participants: Array<{ address: string; displayName?: string }>;\n  lastActivityAt: string;\n};\n```\n\n`create` is non-blocking \u2014 it returns a summary immediately while signer mining runs in the background. `accept` handles manifest read, bundle import, and peer-feed registration atomically. `leave` is local-only in v1.",
        "updatedAt": "2026-05-13T13:00:29.000Z"
      },
      "timestampUtcMs": "2026-05-13T13:00:29.000Z"
    }
  },
